params._name: The name of the schema to retrieve.

returns._0: The keccak256 hash of the name, used as the ID.

owner().details: Returns the address of the current owner.

registerSchema(string,string,string[],ad.details: Only the contract owner can call this function.

params._name: The human-readable name for the schema (e.g., "WeatherByCity").
params._requiredKeys: The list of keys expected in the response.
params._responseParser: The address of the parser contract.
params._urlTemplate: The URL template for the API endpoint.

renounceOwnership().details: Leaves the contract without owner. It will not be possible to call `onlyOwner` functions. Can only be called by the current owner. NOTE: Renouncing ownership will leave the contract without an owner, thereby disabling any functionality that is only available to the owner.

transferOwnership(address).details: Transfers ownership of the contract to a new account (`newOwner`). Can only be called by the current owner.

getSchema(string).notice: Retrieves a schema by its name.

getSchemaId(string).notice: Computes the schema ID from a name.

registerSchema(string,string,string[],ad.notice: Registers or updates an API schema.
